\subsection{Non-Parametric Validation via Permutation Range Test}

\subsubsection{Motivation for Non-Parametric Framework}
As established in the formal assumption testing in Section 2.2.2, the Shapiro-Francia tests and subsequent QQ-plots revealed significant, systematic departures from normality across all AL Central groups ($p_{SF} = 0.000$). To satisfy the core requirement for alternative calculations in the presence of such violations, we deploy a distribution-free \textbf{Monte Carlo Permutation Test}. This approach is inherently robust as it does not rely on the $F$-distribution or the assumption of a normal population, making it the superior "Gold Standard" for skewed Statcast contact data.

\subsubsection{Methodology and Custom Test Statistic}
We define a custom test statistic, $T$, designed to measure the total spread (range) of the organizational means. Under the null hypothesis ($H_0$), the team labels are non-informative; therefore, any observed range is purely a product of random sampling.

\begin{equation}
    T = \max_{j}(\bar{X}_{j}) - \min_{j}(\bar{X}_{j})
\end{equation}

By shuffling the team labels across all 31,000+ observations 10,000 times ($nmc=10,000$), we constructed an empirical null distribution for $T$. Our observed range of $T_{obs} = 0.0251$ produced an empirical $p$-value of $0.0021$.

